Explanation

1. sudo
Runs the command with superuser (root) privileges.
Creating users requires administrative permissions.

2. useradd
Linux command used to create a new user account in the system.

3. -e 2026-12-07
-e means expiry date of the account.
Here it sets the user account to expire on 7 December 2026.
After this date, the user cannot log in anymore.

4. james
This is the username being created.
Linux usernames are typically lowercase, which matches the task requirement.

In simple words

This command creates a user named james with root permission and sets the account to automatically expire on 7 Dec 2026.

Optional verification command
sudo chage -l james

This command shows account aging details, including the expiry date.
